==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kindling
<hw>Kin"dling</hw> <pr>(k⟦icr⟧n"dl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of causing to burn, or of exciting or inflaming
the passions.</def></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Materials, easily lighted, for starting a fire, such
as small twigs or paper; -- also used in the <pluf>pl.</pluf>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kindly</ent>⟦br⟧
